## 2. THE ERROR

### Symptom
Every `npm run build` on Vercel fails with:

```
Error occurred prerendering page "/_not-found". Read more: https://nextjs.org/docs/messages/prerender-error

[Error: An error occurred in the Server Components render. The specific message
is omitted in production builds to avoid leaking sensitive details. A digest
property is included on this error instance which may provide additional details
about the nature of the error.] {
  digest: '2150316170'
}

Export encountered an error on /_not-found/page: /_not-found, exiting the build.
⨯ Next.js build worker exited with code: 1 and signal: null
Error: Command "npm run build" exited with 1
```

### When Nextra Layout Is Removed
When Nextra's `<Layout>` is removed from `app/layout.tsx`, a **different** error appears:

```
Error occurred prerendering page "/ai-research/manus". Read more: https://nextjs.org/docs/messages/prerender-error

Error: Missing ConfigContext.Provider
    at j (.next/server/chunks/7223.js:3:518)
    at J (.next/server/chunks/7223.js:1:19720) {
  digest: '3787026921'
}
```

This confirms: **Nextra's `ConfigContext.Provider` is required by all `.mdx` pages, but Nextra's `<Layout>` (which provides it) crashes during `/_not-found` prerender.**

---

## 3. ROOT CAUSE ANALYSIS

### Primary Root Cause
**Nextra 4.x's `<Layout>` component from `nextra-theme-docs` crashes when Next.js 15.5.x attempts to statically prerender the `/_not-found` page.**

The `/_not-found` page is *always* prerendered by Next.js 15 during the build step. It renders inside the root `layout.tsx`. If the root layout contains `<Layout>` from `nextra-theme-docs`, that component throws an unrecoverable error during static rendering.

The error is React Server Components-related and is minified in production builds (digest `2150316170`). In the un-minified form (confirmed by removing Nextra Layout), the error is `Missing ConfigContext.Provider` — meaning the Nextra theme expects certain context that doesn't exist during the static prerender of a synthetic page like `/_not-found`.

### Why It Worked Before (Theory — HIGH CONFIDENCE)
The last successful deploy (`dpl_3tyB64Rx5QnaisQnshptAhdR2U`, commit `612f553e`) built with **Node.js 24.x** and had a populated build cache. Every subsequent deploy shows:

```
[4] Skipping build cache since Node.js version changed from "24.x" to "22.x"
```

Vercel dropped Node 24.x support (or the project's `nodeVersion: 24.x` setting stopped being honored). The cache invalidation forced a **full rebuild from scratch**, which hit the Nextra prerender bug that was previously hidden by cached build output.

**Evidence chain:**
1. All deploys since the cache invalidation fail — even with zero code changes
2. A minimal layout with only `<Layout>` + hardcoded pageMap (no custom code at all) also fails
3. Removing `<Layout>` changes the error to `Missing ConfigContext.Provider` on content pages
4. The error is always on a prerendered page, never at compile time

### Contributing Factor: 1,285 Content Files
The Keystatic collection has 1,285 `.mdoc` files (1,181 from genspark imports + 104 original). While the nav tree filter reduces sidebar items to ~104, the Keystatic reader still loads all 1,285 at build time. This may contribute to memory pressure but is NOT the primary crash cause (the minimal layout test proved this).

---

## 4. FILE ARCHITECTURE (Relevant to the Fix)

```
knowledge-base-nextra/
├── app/
│   ├── layout.tsx              ← ROOT LAYOUT — contains Nextra <Layout> (crash point)
│   ├── page.tsx                ← Home page
│   ├── not-found.tsx           ← Custom 404 (added during debugging)
│   ├── [[...slug]]/page.tsx    ← Catch-all for Keystatic docs
│   ├── ai-research/            ← Static MDX pages
│   │   ├── page.mdx
│   │   └── manus/page.mdx
│   ├── genspark/page.mdx
│   ├── kb/                     ← Supabase-backed KB pages
│   │   ├── page.tsx
│   │   ├── [category]/page.tsx
│   │   └── item/[id]/page.tsx
│   ├── keystatic/              ← Admin editor
│   ├── import/page.tsx
│   └── api/keystatic/          ← Keystatic API route
├── components/
│   ├── AppShell.tsx            ← Pass-through (auth removed)
│   ├── UserMenu.tsx            ← Returns null (auth removed)
│   ├── KBChatAssistant.tsx     ← Floating AI chat widget
│   ├── InsightProfitEnterpriseShell.tsx
│   ├── SafeDocRenderer.tsx     ← Custom Markdoc renderer (replaces KeystaticRenderer)
│   └── Sidebar.tsx             ← NEW: custom sidebar (from latest fix attempt)
├── lib/
│   ├── keystatic.ts            ← Safe reader with fallback
│   └── page-map.ts             ← Builds sidebar nav tree from Keystatic docs
├── content/docs/               ← 1,285 .mdoc files
├── keystatic.config.tsx        ← Collection definitions
├── next.config.mjs             ← Nextra wrapper + CSP headers
├── sentry.server.config.ts
├── sentry.client.config.ts
└── package.json
```

### Critical File: `app/layout.tsx` (Original Working Version)
The root layout:
1. Calls `getNavTree()` → reads 1,285 docs from Keystatic → filters to ~104 → converts to pageMap
2. Wraps children in `<Layout>` from `nextra-theme-docs` with `pageMap`, `<Navbar>`, footer
3. Includes `<AppShell>` (pass-through), `<UserMenu>` (null), `<KBChatAssistant>`, `<InsightProfitEnterpriseShell>`

### Critical File: `next.config.mjs`
```js
import nextra from "nextra";
const withNextra = nextra({ latex: false, defaultShowCopyCode: true });
export default withNextra(nextConfig);
```

The `nextra()` wrapper modifies the webpack config and adds the Nextra MDX pipeline.

